<br>
But I do have one proposal:<br>
<br>
Characters should be allowed to change their religion once, just like we can change our alignment once, so long as it's a religion that meets with their race/class combination.<br>
<br>
On Sullon Zek, there are a NPC Missionaries of each diety.  There, the Missionaries a) give followers magical bracelets which display the character's faith and b) give rewards for slaying enemies.  On our server, I'd put Missionaries in the churches and temples on our server who you could go to to change your religion.<br>
<br>
This would make playing a Cleric, Shaman, or Druid, or other &quot;devout&quot; character (Monks? Rangers? Paladins?) more meaningful, in that converting PCs would become a possibility.<br>
<br>
And, I think, this is a suggestion that should, at least in theory, enhance roleplaying.<br>
<br>
Lasgalen, Nineteenth Autumn Initiate of Tunare <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 71<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/27/02 5:28:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1206.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules Change Proposal: Religious Conversion</span><hr size=1> Interesting idea..... I started a character on Sullon Zek, but was not aware about the Missionary bracelet things. I need to learn more about them to see if they are something I'd agree with. <br>
<br>
On a related note: <br>
<br>
Verant, PLEASE let us con another character and determine their relative alignment, if not their exact alignment. <br>
<br>
On Sullon for example, someone on the evil deities group would con as threatening to a player who had a character from the good deities group. Something to that effect. <br>
<br>
There are a few benefits to this, and no really solid disadvantages that I can think of --- <br>
<br>
Benefit #1) Expedites role playing, it distinguishes friend or foe, distinguishes good from evil, etc. <br>
<br>
Benefit #2) It tells us whom we can group with before we waste time or annoy anyone trying to invite a person of vastly different alignment. If I am an an evil character and seeking other evil chars to group with, then being able to con fellow evils from 200 yards away help quicken my search. <br>
<br>
Benefit #3) It allows GUILD LEADERS to confirm and determine just who qualifies to your &quot;evil role playing guild&quot; or your &quot;goody-good role playing guild&quot;. General looks are deceiving. A necromancer does not always look like a necromancer unless he has a skeleton following him. And how do you know that &quot;warrior&quot; is not really a heinous Paladin that is the bane and rival or many evil-based guilds? <br>
<br>
Disadvantage #1) People will complain that this conning system will reveal information they sometimes do not want shared to others.... hmmm, maybe the ANON tag could work to actually hide this if people wanted to remain incognito? Just a thought. I know we are currently at permanent RP tag mode..... but does anyone know if the ANON tag serves *any* functionality on this server? <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aradil>Aradil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/27/02 5:45:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1206.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules Change Proposal: Religious Conversion</span><hr size=1> You can't go /anon while you're /role. So you can't ever go /anon.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/urobingoodfellow.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Robin Goodfellow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 106<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/27/02 5:59:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1206.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rules Change Proposal: Religious Conversion</span><hr size=1> Actually, I miss SZ's player /con, too.<br>
